ol.li:
s'(a) is positive whenever 0 \le a \lt \frac{1}{2};
s'(a) to be negative whenever
\frac{1}{2} \lt a \lt 2;
s'(\frac{1}{2}) = 0.

Since s(t) = -16t^2 + 16t + 32 = -16(t^2 - t - 2) = -16(t-2)(t+1),
s has t-intercepts at (2,0) and (-1,0);
the s-intercept is clearly (0,32);
and the vertex is (\frac{1}{2},36).
See more in part (d).
